38924>>>
38924>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
38924>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
38924>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
38924>>>        Case Begin
38924>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
38926>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
38926>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
38926>>>                Case Break
38927>>>                
38927>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
38930>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
38930>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
38930>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
38930>>>                Case Break
38931>>>                
38931>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
38934>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
38934>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
38934>>>                Case Break
38935>>>                
38935>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
38935>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
38935>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
38935>>>                  
38935>>>        Case End
38935>>>
38935>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
38935>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
38935>>>        Send SetActionButtons
38936>>>
38936>>>        If (HasRecord(Server(Self))) Begin 
38938>>>            Send SetHeaderCaption    ("Equipo:"*equipo.Nombre)
38939>>>            Send SetBreadcrumbCaption equipo.Nombre
38940>>>        End
38940>>>>
38940>>>        Else Begin 
38941>>>            Send SetHeaderCaption     "Nuevo equipo"
38942>>>            Send SetBreadcrumbCaption "Nuevo"
38943>>>        End
38943>>>>
38943>>>    End_Procedure
38944>>>
