39414>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
39414>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
39414>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
39417>>>
39417>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
39417>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
39417>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
39417>>>        Case Begin
39417>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
39419>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
39419>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
39419>>>                Case Break
39420>>>                
39420>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
39423>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
39423>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
39423>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
39423>>>                Case Break
39424>>>                
39424>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
39427>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
39427>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
39427>>>                Case Break
39428>>>                
39428>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
39428>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
39428>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
39428>>>                  
39428>>>        Case End
39428>>>
39428>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
39428>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
39428>>>        Send SetActionButtons
39429>>>
39429>>>        If (HasRecord(Server(Self))) Begin 
39431>>>            Send SetHeaderCaption    ("Entrenador:"*entrenador.Nombre)
39432>>>            Send SetBreadcrumbCaption entrenador.Nombre
39433>>>        End
39433>>>>
39433>>>        Else Begin 
39434>>>            Send SetHeaderCaption     "Nuevo entrenador"
39435>>>            Send SetBreadcrumbCaption "Nuevo"
39436>>>        End
39436>>>>
39436>>>    End_Procedure
39437>>>
39437>>>End_Object
